Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a topology-based approach to formal verification of spatial properties using a logic stemming from the tradition of topological interpretations of modal logics.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with collective adaptive systems, which are often studied in the field of AI.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper mentions graph-based structures and model checking procedures, which are relevant to the field of data structures and algorithms.
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is another possible category as the paper deals with collective operators and properties of systems distributed in physical space, which are relevant to the field of multi-agent systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with systems distributed in physical space and collective adaptive systems, which are relevant to the field of systems and control.
